âœ” Confirms that key access is being enforced correctly.

ğŸ”¹ Summary of Validation Steps
Step	Command	Expected Outcome
1ï¸âƒ£ Check Encryption Zone	hdfs crypto -listZones	Shows /secure_zone as an Encryption Zone.
2ï¸âƒ£ Verify File Metadata	hdfs dfs -getfacl /secure_zone/myfile.txt	Confirms encryption is applied.
3ï¸âƒ£ Test Unauthorized Access	sudo -u unauthorized_user hdfs dfs -cat /secure_zone/myfile.txt	Access denied.
4ï¸âƒ£ Locate Raw Data Blocks	hdfs fsck /secure_zone/myfile.txt -files -blocks	Identifies HDFS block ID.
5ï¸âƒ£ Inspect DataNode Block	cat /hdfs/data/dn/.../blk_*	Encrypted data only.
6ï¸âƒ£ Access Raw Encrypted Data	hdfs dfs -cat /.reserved/raw/secure_zone/myfile.txt	Shows encrypted output.
7ï¸âƒ£ Monitor Key Access in Ranger KMS	tail -f /var/log/ranger/kms/audit.log	Tracks decryption requests.
ğŸ”¹ Conclusion
âœ” HDFS Encryption Zones ensure that data remains encrypted at rest.
âœ” DataNodes store only encrypted blocks, preventing unauthorized access.
âœ” Only authorized users can decrypt and access the file via KMS.
âœ” Using .reserved/raw/ confirms that data is encrypted at the filesystem level.
âœ” Audit logs in Ranger KMS provide visibility into key usage and access violations.
